WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.229 --> 00:00:04.700
&gt;&gt;Narrator:The world we live in contains greater
challenges and greater opportunities than

00:00:04.700 --> 00:00:10.549
at any time in human history. While the global
financial crisis is impacting citizens and

00:00:10.549 --> 00:00:16.129
families around the world, it's also prompting
government, companies and leaders to look

00:00:16.129 --> 00:00:18.070
for fresh solutions.

00:00:18.070 --> 00:00:23.539
This year at The World Economic Forum in Davos,
Switzerland, leading thinkers from all walks

00:00:23.539 --> 00:00:28.869
of life will come together to examine solutions
to the problems we face and they want you

00:00:28.869 --> 00:00:34.190
to be part of the discussion and have a chance
to attend Davos yourself; all expenses paid.

00:00:34.190 --> 00:00:36.309
&gt;&gt; We just have to keep the hope alive.

00:00:36.309 --> 00:00:40.309
&gt;&gt;Narrator: The theme for this year's forum
is "Shaping The Post-Crisis World."

00:00:40.309 --> 00:00:41.359
&gt;&gt; Hello, You Tube.

00:00:41.359 --> 00:00:44.769
&gt;&gt;Dominic Waray: Hello, You Tube. My name
is Dominic Waray and I'm head of environmental

00:00:44.769 --> 00:00:46.340
initiatives at the world economic forum.

00:00:46.340 --> 00:00:48.879
&gt;&gt;Maria Bartaroma: Hello, You Tube. I'm Maria
Bartaroma from CNBC.

00:00:48.879 --> 00:00:52.929
&gt;&gt;Christiana Amanpour: I'm Christiana Amanpour
and I'm going to be at the world economic

00:00:52.929 --> 00:00:55.519
forum in Davos, Switzerland January 29th.

00:00:55.519 --> 00:01:00.739
&gt;&gt;Narrator: The leaders in Davos will be debating
key issues relating to the economy, the environment,

00:01:00.739 --> 00:01:07.230
politics and ethics. You can join that debate
by voting on four basic questions posted on

00:01:07.230 --> 00:01:14.260
YouTube.com/Davos. And you can go further.
Upload a video with your answer to one or

00:01:14.260 --> 00:01:19.720
all of these questions The best video overall
will get to join the most influential people

00:01:19.720 --> 00:01:22.890
in the world at Davos, all expenses paid.

00:01:22.890 --> 00:01:29.240
&gt;&gt; The developed world needs to severely curb
our consumption of materials and energy.

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:34.140
&gt;&gt; Everyone got the wrong individual perspective
of how they sees things and how they see the

00:01:34.140 --> 00:01:35.140
world.

00:01:35.140 --> 00:01:38.501
&gt;&gt; It's very personal for me. It's not just
just political, it's not just public. I see

00:01:38.501 --> 00:01:41.370
what's happening and we have to reverse it.

00:01:41.370 --> 00:01:46.570
&gt;&gt;Narrator: So submit your video today. The
deadline is 20 January 2009.

00:01:46.570 --> 00:01:50.450
Engage. Debate. Attend.

00:01:50.450 --> 00:01:58.689
Have your say on the most pressing questions
at Davos at YouTube.com/Davos.

